name: CoverageEligibilityResponse
description: This resource provides eligibility and plan details from the processing of an CoverageEligibilityRequest resource.

element.definition: This resource provides eligibility and plan details from the processing of an CoverageEligibilityRequest resource.

constraint.human: If the resource is contained in another resource, it SHALL NOT contain nested Resources
If a resource is contained in another resource, it SHALL NOT have a meta.versionId or a meta.lastUpdated
If the resource is contained in another resource, it SHALL be referred to from elsewhere in the resource or SHALL refer to the containing resource
constraint.expression: contained.where((('#'+id in (%resource.descendants().reference | %resource.descendants().as(canonical) | %resource.descendants().as(uri) | %resource.descendants().as(url))) or descendants().where(reference = '#').exists() or descendants().where(as(canonical) = '#').exists() or descendants().where(as(canonical) = '#').exists()).not()).trace('unmatched', id).empty()

extension.valueMarkdown: When a resource has no narrative, only systems that fully understand the data can display the resource to a human safely. Including a human readable representation in the resource makes for a much more robust eco-system and cheaper handling of resources by intermediary systems. Some ecosystems restrict distribution of resources to only those systems that do fully understand the resources, and as a consequence implementers may believe that the narrative is superfluous. However experience shows that such eco-systems often open up to new participants over time.

constraint.human: A resource should have narrative for robust management
If a resource is contained in another resource, it SHALL NOT have a security label

element.definition: The logical id of the resource, as used in the URL for the resource. Once assigned, this value never changes.
element.comment: The only time that a resource does not have an id is when it is being submitted to the server using a create operation.

element.definition: The metadata about the resource. This is content that is maintained by the infrastructure. Changes to the content might not always be associated with version changes to the resource.

element.short: A set of rules under which this content was created
element.definition: A reference to a set of rules that were followed when the resource was constructed, and which must be understood when processing the content. Often, this is a reference to an implementation guide that defines the special rules along with other profiles etc.
element.comment: Asserting this rule set restricts the content to be only understood by a limited set of trading partners. This inherently limits the usefulness of the data in the long term. However, the existing health eco-system is highly fractured, and not yet ready to define, collect, and exchange data in a generally computable sense. Wherever possible, implementers and/or specification writers should avoid using this element. Often, when used, the URL is a reference to an implementation guide that defines these special rules as part of it's narrative along with other profiles, value sets, etc.
element.isModifierReason: This element is labeled as a modifier because the implicit rules may provide additional knowledge about the resource that modifies it's meaning or interpretation

element.definition: The base language in which the resource is written.
element.comment: Language is provided to support indexing and accessibility (typically, services such as text to speech use the language tag). The html language tag in the narrative applies  to the narrative. The language tag on the resource may be used to specify the language of other presentations generated from the data in the resource. Not all the content has to be in the base language. The Resource.language should not be assumed to apply to the narrative automatically. If a language is specified, it should it also be specified on the div element in the html (see rules in HTML5 for information about the relationship between xml:lang and the html lang attribute).

binding.description: A human language.

element.short: Text summary of the resource, for human interpretation
element.definition: A human-readable narrative that contains a summary of the resource and can be used to represent the content of the resource to a human. The narrative need not encode all the structured data, but is required to contain sufficient detail to make it "clinically safe" for a human to just read the narrative. Resource definitions may define what content should be represented in the narrative to ensure clinical safety.
element.comment: Contained resources do not have narrative. Resources that are not contained SHOULD have a narrative. In some cases, a resource may only have text with little or no additional discrete data (as long as all minOccurs=1 elements are satisfied).  This may be necessary for data from legacy systems where information is captured as a "text blob" or where text is additionally entered raw or narrated and encoded information is added later.

element.definition: These resources do not have an independent existence apart from the resource that contains them - they cannot be identified independently, and nor can they have their own independent transaction scope.
element.comment: This should never be done when the content can be identified properly, as once identification is lost, it is extremely difficult (and context dependent) to restore it again. Contained resources may have profiles and tags In their meta elements, but SHALL NOT have security labels.

element.definition: Financial instruments for reimbursement for the health care products and services.
element.comment: All insurance coverages for the patient which may be applicable for reimbursement, of the products and services listed in the claim, are typically provided in the claim to allow insurers to confirm the ordering of the insurance coverages relative to local 'coordination of benefit' rules. One coverage (and only one) with 'focal=true' is to be used in the adjudication of this claim. Coverages appearing before the focal Coverage in the list, and where 'subrogation=false', should provide a reference to the ClaimResponse containing the adjudication results of the prior claim.
element.requirements: There must be at least one coverage for which eligibility is requested.

element.comment: Examples include Medical Care, Periodontics, Renal Dialysis, Vision Coverage.

element.comment: Code to indicate the Professional Service or Product supplied (e.g. CTP, HCPCS, USCLS, ICD10, NCPDP, DIN, RxNorm, ACHI, CCI).
element.requirements: Needed to convey the actual service or product for which eligibility is sought.

binding.description: Allowable service and product codes.

element.definition: Item typification or modifiers codes to convey additional context for the product or service.

binding.description: Item type or modifiers codes, eg for Oral whether the treatment is cosmetic or associated with TMJ, or an appliance was lost or stolen.

element.definition: The practitioner who is eligible for the provision of the product or service.
element.requirements: Needed to convey the eligible provider.

element.definition: True if the indicated class of service is excluded from the plan, missing or False indicates the product or service is included in the coverage.
element.requirements: Needed to identify items that are specifically excluded from the coverage.

element.definition: A short name or tag for the benefit.
element.comment: For example: MED01, or DENT2.
element.requirements: Required to align with other plan names.

element.short: Description of the benefit or services covered
element.definition: A richer description of the benefit or services covered.
element.comment: For example 'DENT2 covers 100% of basic, 50% of major but excludes Ortho, Implants and Cosmetic services'.
element.requirements: Needed for human readable reference.

element.definition: Is a flag to indicate whether the benefits refer to in-network providers or out-of-network providers.
element.requirements: Needed as in or out of network providers are treated differently under the coverage.

binding.description: Code to classify in or out of network services.

element.definition: Indicates if the benefits apply to an individual or to the family.
element.requirements: Needed for the understanding of the benefits.

binding.description: Unit covered/serviced - individual or family.

element.definition: The term or period of the values such as 'maximum lifetime benefit' or 'maximum annual visits'.
element.requirements: Needed for the understanding of the benefits.

binding.description: Coverage unit - annual, lifetime.

element.definition: Benefits used to date.

element.comment: Code to indicate the Professional Service or Product supplied (e.g. CTP, HCPCS, USCLS, ICD10, NCPDP, DIN, RxNorm, ACHI, CCI).
element.requirements: Needed to convey the actual service or product for which eligibility is sought.

binding.description: Allowable service and product codes.

element.definition: Item typification or modifiers codes to convey additional context for the product or service.
element.comment: For example in Oral whether the treatment is cosmetic or associated with TMJ, or for Medical whether the treatment was outside the clinic or out of office hours.
element.requirements: To support provision of the item or to charge an elevated fee.

binding.description: Item type or modifiers codes, eg for Oral whether the treatment is cosmetic or associated with TMJ, or an appliance was lost or stolen.

element.definition: The practitioner who is eligible for the provision of the product or service.
element.requirements: Needed to convey the eligible provider.

element.definition: True if the indicated class of service is excluded from the plan, missing or False indicates the product or service is included in the coverage.
element.requirements: Needed to identify items that are specifically excluded from the coverage.

element.definition: A short name or tag for the benefit.
element.comment: For example: MED01, or DENT2.
element.requirements: Required to align with other plan names.

element.short: Description of the benefit or services covered
element.definition: A richer description of the benefit or services covered.
element.comment: For example 'DENT2 covers 100% of basic, 50% of major but excludes Ortho, Implants and Cosmetic services'.
element.requirements: Needed for human readable reference.

element.definition: Is a flag to indicate whether the benefits refer to in-network providers or out-of-network providers.
element.requirements: Needed as in or out of network providers are treated differently under the coverage.

binding.description: Code to classify in or out of network services.

element.definition: Indicates if the benefits apply to an individual or to the family.
element.requirements: Needed for the understanding of the benefits.

binding.description: Unit covered/serviced - individual or family.

element.definition: The term or period of the values such as 'maximum lifetime benefit' or 'maximum annual visits'.
element.requirements: Needed for the understanding of the benefits.

binding.description: Coverage unit - annual, lifetime.

element.definition: Benefits used to date.
Classification of benefit being provided.
element.comment: For example: deductible, visits, benefit amount.
element.requirements: Needed to convey the nature of the benefit.

binding.description: Deductable, visits, co-pay, etc.

element.definition: The quantity of the benefit which is permitted under the coverage.
element.requirements: Needed to convey the benefits offered under the coverage.

element.definition: The quantity of the benefit which have been consumed to date.
element.requirements: Needed to convey the benefits consumed to date.

element.definition: A boolean flag indicating whether a preauthorization is required prior to actual service delivery.
element.requirements: Needed to convey that preauthorization is required.

element.definition: Codes or comments regarding information or actions associated with the preauthorization.
element.requirements: Needed to inform the provider of collateral materials or actions needed for preauthorization.

binding.description: Type of supporting information to provide with a preauthorization.

element.definition: A web location for obtaining requirements or descriptive information regarding the preauthorization.
element.requirements: Needed to enable insurers to advise providers of informative information.

element.definition: A reference from the Insurer to which these services pertain to be used on further communication and as proof that the request occurred.
element.requirements: To provide any preauthorization reference for provider use.

element.definition: A code for the form to be used for printing the content.
element.comment: May be needed to identify specific jurisdictional forms.
element.requirements: Needed to specify the specific form used for producing output for this response.

binding.description: The forms codes.

element.definition: Errors encountered during the processing of the request.
element.requirements: Need to communicate processing issues to the requestor.

element.definition: An error code,from a specified code system, which details why the eligibility check could not be performed.
element.requirements: Required to convey processing errors.

binding.description: The error codes for adjudication processing.
